SIMPLE: prophesy
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Prophesy
<hw>Proph"e*sy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Prophesied</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Prophesying</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>.]</vmorph> <ety>[See
<er>Prophecy</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To foretell; to predict; to
prognosticate.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He doth not <qex>prophesy</qex> good concerning me.</q> <rj><au>1
Kings xxii. 8.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Then I perceive that will be verified⟦br⟧
Henry the Fifth did sometime <qex>prophesy</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To foreshow; to herald; to prefigure.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Methought thy very gait did <qex>prophesy</qex>⟦br⟧
A royal nobleness; I must embrace thee.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Prophesy</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Prophesy
<hw>Proph"e*sy</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>To utter predictions; to make declaration of events
to come.</def> <rj><au>Matt. xv. 7.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p> <sn>2.</sn> <def>To give instruction in religious matters; to
interpret or explain Scripture or religious subjects; to preach; to
exhort; to expound.</def> <rj><au>Ezek. xxxvii. 7.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Prophet</ent>⟦br⟧
